The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in image recognition and proposes a novel explanation for their robustness. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also draws on lessons learned from natural language processing (NLP), indicating that it may also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents a new deep CNN frame interpolation architecture, which suggests that it may be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
